// Every user has its personal page where they can mange list of collections (create new, delete, or edit) — each collection in the list is a link to the collection page that contains table of items with sorting/filtering and capabilities to create new item, edit or delete existing item).
import { Col, Container, Row, Card, Button } from "react-bootstrap";
const UserPage = () => {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Row>
        <Col>
          <Card>
            <Card.Body>
              <Card.Title>All Collection List</Card.Title>
              <Link to="/collection">Collection 1(4)</Link>
              <Link to="/collection">Collection 2(4)</Link>
              <Link to="/collection">Collection 3(4)</Link>
            </Card.Body>
          </Card>
        </Col>
      </Row>
      <Row>
        <Col>
          <Card>
            <Card.Body>
              <Card.Title>Add New Collection</Card.Title>
              <Button>Create Collection</Button>
            </Card.Body>
          </Card>
        </Col>
      </Row>
    </Container>
  );
};

export default UserPage;
